item.title: Shoulder french rack
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Prepared from a square cut shoulder by removing the blade, leaving the underlying muscles attached. The ribs are cut to a specified length.
item.content:encoded: Prepared from a square cut shoulder by removing the blade, leaving the underlying muscles attached. The ribs are cut to a specified length.

item.title: Tenderloin boneless
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: The full length tenderloin is taken from a chump-on loin or a boneless side. Side muscle is generally removed.
item.content:encoded: The full length tenderloin is taken from a chump-on loin or a boneless side. Side muscle is generally removed.

item.title: Long loin
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Cut from a 8 rib chump-off saddle by sawing along the backbone. The flap is removed a specified distance from the eye of the meat.
item.content:encoded: Cut from a 8 rib chump-off saddle by sawing along the backbone. The flap is removed a specified distance from the eye of the meat.

item.title: Hindshank
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Prepared from a bone-in leg by a straight cut through the stifle joint. The knuckle tip is removed.
item.content:encoded: Prepared from a bone-in leg by a straight cut through the stifle joint. The knuckle tip is removed.

item.title: Leg bone IN
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Taken from a bone-in side. Separated by a straight cut at right angles to the line of the back between the 5th and 6th lumbar vertebrae.
item.content:encoded: Taken from a bone-in side. Separated by a straight cut at right angles to the line of the back between the 5th and 6th lumbar vertebrae.

item.title: Short loin
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: The 1 rib bone-in loin remains after the 7th rib rack is removed from the 8 rib chump-off long loin.
item.content:encoded: The 1 rib bone-in loin remains after the 7th rib rack is removed from the 8 rib chump-off long loin.

item.title: Loin boneless
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: The eye of meat from a 1 rib short loin with silverskin off.
item.content:encoded: The eye of meat from a 1 rib short loin with silverskin off.

item.title: Leg boneless
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Prepared from a chump-on, shank off-leg by removing the aitch bone and sacral vertebrae, and by removing the femur bone.
item.content:encoded: Prepared from a chump-on, shank off-leg by removing the aitch bone and sacral vertebrae, and by removing the femur bone.

item.title: Flap
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: The bone-in flap consists of the abdominal wall tissues and rib ends.
item.content:encoded: The bone-in flap consists of the abdominal wall tissues and rib ends.

item.title: Rack Frenched
item.dc:creator: admin
item.description: Cut from an 8 rib chump-off long loin, leaving a short loin and the 7 rib rack.
item.content:encoded: Cut from an 8 rib chump-off long loin, leaving a short loin and the 7 rib rack.
